x4freetext: Pulse-height spectra of the scattered charged

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Errors are estimated to be smaller than 5%
in relative cross sections and less than 10% in the
absolute magnitude of the cross section. For elastic
scattering the errors due to counting statistics were
very small, and the estimate of delta sigma was
obtained from the reproducibility of the data points.
For the proton data the major contributions to delta
sigma include the counting statistics and, at least
for proton groups with Q < 3 MeV, the estimation of
the error associated with the (subjective) separation
of adjacent peaks in the pulse-height spectra. The
absolute error assigned to the measured cross
sections depended on the measured target thickness,
